verses.roman:
mahā-yogeśvara ācārya--tarajāte samartha
āmiha bujhite nāri tarajāra artha'

synonyms: mahā-yogeśvara—the greatest mystic; ācārya—Advaita Ācārya; tarajāte samartha—very expert in writing sonnets; āmiha—and yet I; bujhite—to understand; nāri—am not able; tarajāra—of the sonnet; artha—the meaning.
translation: "Advaita Ācārya is a great mystic. No one can understand Him. He is expert in writing sonnets that even I Myself cannot understand."
